ISLAMABAD, Jan 03 (APP): Minister for Energy Hammad Azhar on Monday said the PML-N government turned the country’s electricity on imported fuel and now their prices has surged in the international market.
Responding to a tweet of PML-N leader Miftah Ismail, he said, “For your (Miftah) information, the fuel cost adjustment is being done due the fuel of your imported LNG and coal power plants”.
